  "text": "The automorphism group Aut(Z /2N Z) acts on vector valued modular forms f = r f r e r for ρ orρ by f σ = r f r e σ(r) . The elements of Aut(Z /2N Z) are all involutions, also called Atkin-Lehner involutions, and correspond to the exact divisors c || N (i.e., c | N and (c, N/c) = 1). The automorphism σ c corresponding to c is defined by the equations σ c (r) ≡ −r (2c) and σ c (r) ≡ r (2N/c) [CITATION_1] for r ∈ Z /2N Z, compare [CITATION_2] , Theorem 5.2. Note that the Atkin-Lehner involutions only permute the components of a vector valued modular form.",
